results.name: Triangle: number of exactly (m-1)-dimensional partitions of n, up to conjugacy, for n >= 1, m >= 0.
comment: The partition of 1 is considered to be dimension -1 by convention.
Partitions are considered as generalized Ferrers diagrams; any permutation of the axes produces a conjugate.
xref: Reversed triangle is A119339. Columns stabilize to A118364.
results.author: _Franklin T. Adams-Watters_, May 11 2006
